Its 2017 and the news headlines are full of political noise. Trump to be impeached? Brexit to ruin the UK economy? Macron to save the Euro? Xi Jinping to fix the Chinese economy? Zuma to be replaced by Dlamini-Zuma? What does it all mean? Should you sell out your portfolio and go and live in a cave!?
.
.
We discuss these pressing issues on HotStocks tonight at 8h00 pm, on CNBC Africa (DStv channel 410). The show is hosted by Bronwyn Nielsen and Paul Theron. No guest today.
.
.
In general, Paul's advice is to stay the course. Keep calm and carry on! To illuminate these issues, we also discuss a few specific companies: Amazon.com, Steinhoff and Curro Holdings. 
Investment of the Day: We have a bit of free cash in the JSE account, so we decide to buy a few more Curro shares. We snap up 255 shares at R43.15 each.

A survey compiled by UBS Wealth Management revealed that 82% of millionaires across the world consider the current period as being the "most unpredictable" ever.

The survey was conducted by Censuswide on behalf of UBS Wealth Management, and covered 2,842 individuals with at least $1m (£771,000) in investable assets across UK, Italy, Switzerland, Mexico, Hong Kong, Singapore, and Japan.
